# ── DEBUG: Check 0xB5 in output buffer before write ──
if compare rsi_check_pos 0
    add rsi_check_pos 120
    store it into temp3
    load from output at temp3
    if compare it 181
        return 200
    end
end

# ── Write output to stdout ──
# Use addressof to get the output buffer pointer, then syscall directly.
# The syscall handler works for fd (arg1=literal) and count (arg3).
# For buf (arg2), the handler emits mov rsi which has a codegen issue
# in the self-hosted chain. Use addressof to load the address into a
# variable, then pass it as arg2.
addressof output
store it into temp
store output_len into temp2
syscall 1 1 temp temp2

# Exit with success
return 0
